fix: session persistence was crashing the Claude CLI with 'Error: --session-id can only be used with --continue or --resume if --fork-session is also specified.' The SDK has two different options: continue_conversation (continues most recent session) and resume (resumes a specific session by ID). We were setting session_id + continue_conversation, but the CLI wants --resume {id}. Changed to options.resume = session_id. Verified: two messages in same conversation both show same session ID (46af54ce), agent remembers context across turns, memory saved ('User name is Eduardo'), no crashes.
